nd retrieves public members. Furthermore, I consider whether to add metadata and if tests for exercising ClassMap should reflect configurations for test classes. Lastly, I wonder if the native image needs to account for methods.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking reflection metadata**\\n\\nI’m considering how the method on test classes interacts with native images that require reflection metadata. It seems like the agent could produce the necessary test metadata. But hold on, I notice there isn’t a src/test/resources directory to draw from? I should double-check and clarify how the metadata is being handled and whether it’s being generated properly for those classes. It’s essential to ensure everything is set up correctly!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_IxRxzDiCxqvS4ICCmj0mSIRB|fc_09236850308d92d20169f0659cc938819da1557f0358f5aa8b", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "find tests/src/plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.2/src/test -maxdepth 5 -type f -print | sort && find metadata/plexus/plexus-utils -maxdepth 4 -type f -print -exec sh -c 'echo ===$1; sed -n \"1,200p\" \"$1\"' _ {} \\;", "timeout": 10}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1618, "output": 1171, "cacheRead": 31744, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34533, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777362313049, "responseId": "resp_09236850308d92d20169f065898058819daf618aa603921271"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_IxRxzDiCxqvS4ICCmj0mSIRB|fc_09236850308d92d20169f0659cc938819da1557f0358f5aa8b", "toolName": "bash", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "tests/src/plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.2/src/test/java/plexus/plexus_utils/ExceptionUtilsTest.java\ntests/src/plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.2/src/test/java/plexus/plexus_utils/FastMapTest.java\ntests/src/plexus/plexus-utils/1.0.2/src/test/java/plexus/plexus_utils/Plexus_utilsTest.java\ntests/src/